caption: Nice whiskey flats!
While I usually would not like to visit a bar attached to a hotel, the Dignitary was a nice surprise. My group enjoyed some excellent whiskey flights in the relaxed and uncrowded environment.
Great place to have  drink.  Ask for Pete.  Great guy, knowledgeable about whiskey and bourbon.  Always have a smile.

Cosy bar that's perfect for a meet-up with friends. Variety of seating options, including bar seats, tables and couches. They also have a fireplace. Friendly bartenders and servers, and they make stiff drinks. Decent whisky selection, including some from India (!)

What a great bar with several hundred bourbons / ryes / scotches ready to pour.  Nice atmosphere and, best of all, the brands I am familiar with were reasonably price for being attached to a hotel in the middle of DC.
Great, cozy place for late night drinks on a weeknight! Has a Mad Men ambiance but still casual at the same time.
This bar has a nice atmosphere. A bit of an upscale feel.
Cozy and great atmosphere

I wouldn't expect such a good bar in a hotel, even an upscale Marriott. The place was clean and stylish, had a great atmosphere, and friendly staff. They have an impressive selection of whiskey and made a solid (and generously-poured) Manhattan.
Amazing place to meet and talk

This is a super classy looking bar located in the Marriott Marquis. We had just come from a convention nearby and were not quite dressed the part, but the service was still excellent. The charcuterie board was delicious, and they have a great selection of drinks available. I'm usually a little wary of hotel bars and restaurants but this one did not disappoint.
Lovely old school bar with an incredible selection of whiskey. Service is excellent, as are the drinks!
Prices are a little steep
Awesome bourbon bar. Dark atmosphere big leather chairs. Blues music. Bar tenders all knowing and hard working
Great cocktails and whiskey selection, but quite pricey for the quality of creativity and mix-ins. Double the cost the top Baltimore joints.
Extensive Bourbon lineup. Peter is truly skilled in craft cocktails and the nuances of his spirit offerings. Sit at the bar for great conversation and delicious nibbles.
Nice space. Old Fashioned was better in the hotel bar however. Could have been an off night?
Great hotel bar that's a cut above the rest! Seemed to have hundreds of different Bourbons, Scotches and other rare libations and liquors.
Intimate cozy spot. It's well appointed and the drinks are amazing.  I recommend Smoke off the Barrel!
Awesome selection!
Great atmosphere
Great location in the Marriott Marquis however the service is mediocre for the venue
Great place!
Love this place! Great list for bourbon. Great cocktails and friendly staff. Visited while staying at the Marriott.
Wonderful atmosphere
Nice bar and all the bourbon you could imagine.
Love this place! Pete is great!
Great bartender who remembers me from year to year. Good beer selection
Went here for a hospitality function that was put on by a company that was attending a trade show. Great food, atmosphere, & bartenders. Nice bar area. Great time!!
Pricey, but great for and classic drinks.
Great

Located on the ground floor of the Marriott Hotel, the Dignitary is a perfect meeting spot and watering hole when visiting the area or while at the convention center.  Clean space, professionally operated with a great staff.

This is my favorite bar in DC. I've never tried their food; there is no need. I have no idea if there is a happy hour because I truly don't care. If you're looking for the most knowledgeable people who know bourbon, whiskey, and other alcohols - you've come to the right place. Pete and Dave make a team unmatched by any I've ever seen or encountered. Every time I've been here, Pete somehow remembers what I've already had and offers suggestions based on what I like. I now stay at the Marriott Marquis frequently - my experience at this bar makes my stay at the hotel. I can't sing Pete's praise enough. If you're in town and nearby, you owe it to yourself to visit this place. Sit at the bar, ask for Pete. Tell him what you like and sincerely listen to his recommendations. I promise you will not be disappointed.
Great selection of whiskies and scotches. Great staff that knows how to make quality drinks.
Great atmosphere and staff

Miserable service. Three of us ordered whiskey flights (two of them were the exact same) but it took the bartender almost ten minutes to do the pours. He mischarged two of us, and we waited at the bar for another five minutes trying to get someone's attention so we could get our tabs fixed. It felt like staff was avoiding us - the place certainly wasn't busy, with only a few people sitting at the bar and just a handful at tables. One person behind the bar said he couldn't help us, that the original bartender needed to do it, and then scurried away without any attempt to get the correct bartender for us. While we were waiting, we chatted with another customer seated at the bar who had been waiting to close her tab, wallet out, since before we'd arrived. It took a very loud 'excuse me' to finally get someone to tend to us and get our tabs fixed, with a very meager apology. We ordered at around half past the hour, and weren't able to get everything sorted out so we could enjoy our drinks until ten to.  The flights were fine and the atmosphere was pleasantly both cozy and classy, but the bad service far outweighed any of the positives.
Prices are high, but drinks are good. If you're at the Marriott atmosphere is really good as well. Staff are attentive. Exactly what you would want in a medium to high end bar.
My favorite DC whiskey bar.
Awesome! The food is good too
Great! Nice vibe and huge whiskey selection. Pete is a super nice bartender
Great bar for bourbon! The staff knows their stuff.
Great Bar with knowledgeable bartenders

It’s totally fine. But there is no Happy Hour here, not for food nor for drinks. That shouldn’t be advertised when it’s...well...false advertising. I know it’s all fake-news these days, but please don’t mess about with Happy Hour!

Spirits were reasonably priced and the wait staff checked on us, even though we were the only table sitting outside on the patio. How could one complain when you're smoking a cigar and drinking your favorite bourbon.
Outstanding selection of Bourbon
Service was good.  Try the 24 hr pork belly. It was amazing.
Best bartenders
Great whiskey bourbon selection, customer service and ambience

Wonderful burbon selection. Especially due to the fact that some of these labels are almost altogether unavailable to the private buyer.  Pair that with EXPERT knowledge of every selection and it makes for something special.  Its not about the food and its not about buying a domestic beer. There are plenty of places for that (its there however, for the casual stumble in that didnt intend to go to a top flight wiskey bar). It does what its supposed to at a very high level.

Great place for a drink in a relaxed classic atmosphere.  Peter and Tom at the bar know their Scotch and introduced me to some Islay single-malts I'd never had the chance to try.  I will be going back when I am in D.C. again.
Great ambiance and great bar tenders. Not too loud but just enough going on to feel happening!! :-)

A very elegant place. The atmosphere is very pleasant. You can have a nice conversation while enjoying the drinks. I love the whiskey listing.  I am a Washington resident and this bar is like my local bar too. You can meet people from around the country who are in DC for business. The service is very good and special Saba was always smiling and welcoming guests to the bar.  Love it.
Comfortable, dark, great bourbon, had my first Angel's Envy here years ago as recommended by the bald bartender, knows his stuff.
tries not to be a hotel restaurant but doesn't pull it off...
Awesome bar to pass the time while your kids are playing in tournaments at the convention center.  Whiskey and Bourbon selection is great. The two gentlemen bartenders are awesome.
Great Bourbon selection. Great atmosphere.  Tom was awesome!
Old school dark-lit, leather - wrapped, DC bar.
Expensive but great atmosphere

I love hotel bars because a good hotel bar is a great place to people watch and spend an evening.  The dignitary is a great hotel bar.  The bartender was awesome and incredibly helpful with scotch recommendations and explanations
Lovely cocktails

If you enjoy paying $10 (+ taxes and tip) for a beer in a small glass that is not even full, this is the place for you. I'm not talking fancy, strong or imported beers either; just regular strength, US beers. The environment felt really nice, though.
Great hidden gem! Old fashioned is one of the best and they are very accommodating.

Awesome cocktails. Srsly. Food great too. Service was super great early on then they abandoned us. Oh well. Love the atmosphere. I'm from Chicago and it felt like old school boys club minus the sexism.  GO.

After the last google city experts event, my roommate, a friend and I decided to check out the new Marriott hotel.  The hotel lobby is beautiful!  We then decided to have cocktails at The Dignitary.  The prices are typical DC prices.  The atmosphere was very warm and rustic.  I can see us coming back after work and late night drinks!   It does attract more people on business travel.  I travel a lot and wish hotel bars were as swanky as The Dignitary.
